This paper is about unsupervised text attribute transfer, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new framework for text attribute transfer that involves editing entangled latent representations. This involves the use of a Transformer-based autoencoder and an optimization algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, the paper also involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and optimization, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image data sets for evaluation, which could suggest a connection to computer vision and the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
